00:13:20.950 --> 00:13:23.680 align:middle line:84%
to believe-- as many scientists
believe right now-- then what

00:13:23.680 --> 00:13:24.520 align:middle line:90%
is?

00:13:24.520 --> 00:13:27.160 align:middle line:84%
So this is the key
climate change is a fact,

00:13:27.160 --> 00:13:28.350 align:middle line:90%
it's happening.

00:13:28.350 --> 00:13:30.730 align:middle line:84%
But it may not be
happening for the reasons

00:13:30.730 --> 00:13:32.440 align:middle line:90%
that we have suspected.

00:13:32.440 --> 00:13:36.220 align:middle line:84%
So what we're now beginning
to understand parallels,

00:13:36.220 --> 00:13:39.430 align:middle line:84%
in many cases, what our
most ancient and indigenous

00:13:39.430 --> 00:13:41.460 align:middle line:90%
traditions have always told us.

00:13:41.460 --> 00:13:45.730 align:middle line:10%
If you go to the Inuit
elders in the Arctic regions

00:13:45.730 --> 00:13:49.210 align:middle line:10%
and you ask them what it is
that's causing this change,

00:13:49.210 --> 00:13:50.650 align:middle line:10%
they will tell you.

00:13:50.650 --> 00:13:52.810 align:middle line:84%
They will tell you
that the Earth has

00:13:52.810 --> 00:13:56.470 align:middle line:90%
changed her location in space.

00:13:56.470 --> 00:13:59.257 align:middle line:84%
They'll say that
their sky has changed.

00:13:59.257 --> 00:14:00.340 align:middle line:90%
This is the term they use.

00:14:00.340 --> 00:14:02.660 align:middle line:90%
Their sky has changed.

00:14:02.660 --> 00:14:06.520 align:middle line:84%
Well there was an
Australian astronomer.

00:14:06.520 --> 00:14:10.510 align:middle line:10%
His name is Milutin Milankovic
who agrees with this.

00:14:10.510 --> 00:14:14.770 align:middle line:10%
Before he died in 1958,
Milutin Milankovic

00:14:14.770 --> 00:14:18.540 align:middle line:10%
had created a theory that
was discounted at first,

00:14:18.540 --> 00:14:20.680 align:middle line:10%
but it is becoming
more popular now

00:14:20.680 --> 00:14:23.140 align:middle line:10%
because it is telling
us the story that

00:14:23.140 --> 00:14:26.500 align:middle line:10%
matches the data of what
we're actually saying.

00:14:26.500 --> 00:14:31.690 align:middle line:84%
Milutin Milankovic
recognized three big cycles,

00:14:31.690 --> 00:14:35.500 align:middle line:84%
shifts in the location,
of Earth in space.

00:14:35.500 --> 00:14:38.680 align:middle line:84%
Earth, it doesn't stay
stationary as Earth moves

00:14:38.680 --> 00:14:41.260 align:middle line:84%
around the sun, our
planet does a dance.

00:14:41.260 --> 00:14:43.150 align:middle line:84%
There's a tilt, an
angle, and a wobble.

00:14:43.150 --> 00:14:44.400 align:middle line:90%
And they have technical terms.

00:14:44.400 --> 00:14:47.170 align:middle line:84%
And let me just identify
those very quickly.

00:14:47.170 --> 00:14:50.980 align:middle line:84%
One of those is called the
precession of the equinoxes.

00:14:50.980 --> 00:14:55.180 align:middle line:84%
We all heard about precession
during the 2012 phenomenon

00:14:55.180 --> 00:14:56.860 align:middle line:90%
in the Mayan calendar.

00:14:56.860 --> 00:15:00.360 align:middle line:84%
Precessions are about
26,000 years long.

00:15:00.360 --> 00:15:01.930 align:middle line:90%
And our ancestors knew that.

00:15:01.930 --> 00:15:03.310 align:middle line:90%
So that is one of the cycles.

00:15:03.310 --> 00:15:07.470 align:middle line:84%
A second cycle is what
is called eccentricity.

00:15:07.470 --> 00:15:11.880 align:middle line:84%
And what that means is that
as earth moves around the sun,

00:15:11.880 --> 00:15:15.060 align:middle line:84%
it's not a circular orbit,
it is an elliptical orbit.

00:15:15.060 --> 00:15:17.790 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes in the ellipse,
we're closer to the sun.

00:15:17.790 --> 00:15:19.660 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes we're further away.

00:15:19.660 --> 00:15:21.930 align:middle line:84%
That means the cycle
varies when we're close,

00:15:21.930 --> 00:15:23.880 align:middle line:84%
about 41,000 years,
and we're further

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:27.030 align:middle line:90%
apart about 100,000 years.

00:15:27.030 --> 00:15:28.560 align:middle line:90%
That's the second cycle.

00:15:28.560 --> 00:15:32.770 align:middle line:84%
And the third is called
the tilt, or the obliquity.

00:15:32.770 --> 00:15:33.570 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:15:33.570 --> 00:15:38.310 align:middle line:84%
So these three cycles that
Earth is going through

00:15:38.310 --> 00:15:40.750 align:middle line:84%
as it moves around the sun,
now you know what they are.

00:15:40.750 --> 00:15:44.020 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look at them as
they are plotted on a graph.

00:15:44.020 --> 00:15:47.080 align:middle line:84%
You're going to see something
absolutely astounding.

00:15:47.080 --> 00:15:51.120 align:middle line:84%
So what you're seeing in the
graph on your screen right now,

00:15:51.120 --> 00:15:53.520 align:middle line:84%
the red is the precession
of the equinoxes.

00:15:53.520 --> 00:15:55.860 align:middle line:90%
The green is the obliquity.

00:15:55.860 --> 00:15:58.690 align:middle line:84%
And the blue is
the eccentricity.

00:15:58.690 --> 00:16:03.220 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you look closely
as they ebb and flow,

00:16:03.220 --> 00:16:09.610 align:middle line:84%
if either eccentricity or
obliquity or precession,

00:16:09.610 --> 00:16:12.890 align:middle line:84%
if any two of these
rise at the same time,

00:16:12.890 --> 00:16:14.070 align:middle line:90%
look at what happens.

00:16:14.070 --> 00:16:15.790 align:middle line:10%
At the bottom of
the screen, you're

